reviews.review: Actually thought it was better then I expected dit to be. Ona par with the last trilogy, in quality and visual wonder. The Film nicely closes, supposedly, the saga of the Skywalker family with nice send offs to tons of familiar faces, each one bringing a smile to my face. Much like the end of the 2nd trilogy, or is that the first, when we discover and see how Darth Vader became the man behind the mask, both physically as well as mentally, this finale gives us an ending that connects most of the dots. And for the most part does it in a crowd pleasing and enjoyable way. Look folks, they actually pulled it off
Short on dialog very boring first 30 minutes. Played on events from earlier movies but lacked originality.
Great movie!  Plot changes constantly!  Really enjoyed!

If I could give this movie zero stars, I would. I don't understand the fan excitement over thisâ€”TROS is a movie that does everything and nothing all at the same time. A nostalgia trip that somehow regresses each character, promises us things that never pan out, dupes us into thinking that anything in this trilogy was ever planned from the start, and gives our lead the short end of the stick in all aspects. The highlight of the movie was Adam Driver, no doubt putting his all into a shoddy mess of a script that he was given. J.J. Abrams was correct when he said he's really bad at wrapping up film endings.

Poe's character gets more and more annoying.  Everytime he speaks.  also too much predictability and not enough shock.  It had a lot to live up to.  I felt like better acting may have helped in that department.  But acting in Star Wars films has never been Oscar worthy I suppose.

At the end of the day, this is a movie. Granted a saga that has been around for 42 years.  The Palpatine arc is a bit odd but it ties up some loose ends and creates others. This will not be the end of the franchise just the Skywalker saga. Disney did not pat George Lucas 4 billion just to end it with 5 movies and a couple of theme partks
Loved al of the hidden references to past additions and how they tied up loose ends.

Some great visuals, brilliant score and at times excellent acting.. I found the movie was rushed yet by the end it was dragging.. Sadly, I thought there were lots of plot holes and parts made no sense. Could have been so much better.
It was really good but the ending sucked

Very enjoyable.  I will never get tired of Star Wars, but if you're gonna bring back the Emperor then bring back Vader.
